  <text xml:lang="ta" type="edition">
    <body>
      <div xml:id="KT190-kilavi">
        <p type="edition">piriviṭai āṟṟāḷākiya talaimakaḷ tōḻikkuc colliyatu.</p>
        <p type="translation" xml:lang="en">Uttered to the confidante by HER who didn't have the
          strength [anymore] in the time of separation.</p>
      </div>


      <div xml:id="KT190">
        <lg type="edition">
          <l> neṟiyiruṅ katuppoṭu peruntō ṇīvic</l>
          <l> ceṟivaḷai nekiḻac ceyporuṭ kakaṉṟō</l>
          <l> raṟivarkol vāḻi tōḻi poṟivari</l>
          <l> veñciṉa varaviṉ paintalai tumiya</l>
          <l> vuravuru muraṟu maraiyiru ṇaṭunā</l>
          <l> ṇallē ṟiyaṅkutō ṟiyampum</l>
          <l> pallāṉ ṟoḻuvat torumaṇik kuralē.</l>
        </lg>
        <lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
          <l>He who has stroked the big shoulder along with the curly dark hair</l>
          <l>[and] departed to make wealth<note place="foot"><term xml:lang="ta">ceyporuṭku akaṉṟōr</term>:
            literally "who has departed for the sake of the wealth that is to be made".</note>, for
            tight bangles to become loose,</l>
          <l>does he know, oh friend,</l>
          <l rend="indent">
            <choice>
              <seg>of the one bell's voice</seg>
              <seg>[Oh,] the voice of a single bell</seg>
            </choice> in the manger with
            many cows </l>
          <l rend="indent">that sounds each time the good bull stirs</l>
          <l rend="indent">at midnight [after] half of the darkness<note place="foot"><term
                xml:lang="ta">arai iruḷ naṭunāḷ</term>: how exactly to understand this phrase? At
            midnight half of the dark time has already passed?</note>,</l>
          <l rend="indent3">when strong thunder roars,</l>
          <l rend="indent">so that the green<note place="foot"><term xml:lang="ta">paintalai</term>: here the
            question seems legitimate whether this is a misreading of <term xml:lang="ta">paittalai</term>,
            "hooded head", i.e. part of the usual description of the cobra (cf. KT 391.3).</note>
            head of the striped [and] spotted furious<note place="foot"><term xml:lang="ta">poṟi
            varai | vem ciṉa araviṉ</term>: what is the impact of these epithets to <term
                xml:lang="ta">aravu</term>? Are we supposed to recognise the kind of snake?</note></l>
          <l rend="indent4">snake is severed?</l>
        </lg>
      </div>
